HEADWORD: Zygodactylous
<hw>Zyg`o*dac"tyl*ous</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>zygo`n</grk> a yoke, pair + <?/ finger, toe: cf. F.
<ets>zygodactyle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Yoke-footed;
having the toes disposed in pairs; -- applied to birds which have two
toes before and two behind, as the parrot, cuckoo, woodpecker,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

